    //=================================================================================================================
    // WIKI - Game Basics
    //=================================================================================================================
    "MENU_WIKI_GAME_BASICS_Title"                             "Game Basics"
    "MENU_WIKI_GAME_BASICS_Text1"                             "Ancient Arena is cooperative defense against waves of creeps, where player teams fight increasingly powerful enemy waves. Game continues until round 120 or until all players in team are defeated."
    "MENU_WIKI_GAME_BASICS_Subtitle1"                         "Game Objective"
    "MENU_WIKI_GAME_BASICS_Text2"                             "Survive as long as possible by defending against creep waves. Each player has limited number of lives (configurable in lobby). When player loses all lives, they are eliminated. Team loses when all members are eliminated."
    "MENU_WIKI_GAME_BASICS_Subtitle2"                         "Round System"
    "MENU_WIKI_GAME_BASICS_Text3"                             "Each round consists of preparation phase (30 seconds) and combat phase. With each round creeps become stronger - their stats, armor and magic resistance increase. Every few rounds bosses or special events appear."

    //=================================================================================================================
    // WIKI - Heroes and Abilities (combined category)
    //=================================================================================================================
    "MENU_WIKI_HEROES_AND_ABILITIES_Title"                    "Heroes and Abilities"
    "MENU_WIKI_HEROES_AND_ABILITIES_Text1"                    "Everything about hero selection and ability system in Ancient Arena."

    //=================================================================================================================
    // WIKI - Hero Selection
    //=================================================================================================================
    "MENU_WIKI_HERO_SELECTION_Title"                          "Hero Selection"
    "MENU_WIKI_HERO_SELECTION_Text1"                          "Before game starts there is hero selection phase, consisting of ban stage and pick stage. Players with Battle Pass can ban up to 3 heroes."
    "MENU_WIKI_HERO_SELECTION_Subtitle1"                      "Rerolls"
    "MENU_WIKI_HERO_SELECTION_Text2"                          "At game start each player is offered one random hero of each attribute:\n- Strength\n- Agility\n- Intelligence\n- Universal\n\nFrom four presented options you can choose one hero.\nIf offered heroes don't suit you, use 'Reroll' button to refresh entire set and get new random heroes.\n\nAlso available is 'Random' button which instantly selects random hero from entire pool without preview.\n\nNumber of available rerolls is set in lobby settings and can be from 0 to 100."
    "MENU_WIKI_HERO_SELECTION_Subtitle2"                      "SSS Category"
    "MENU_WIKI_HERO_SELECTION_Text3"                          "Some heroes and abilities belong to SSS category — these are especially powerful heroes and abilities with unique mechanics.\n\nIn first round random abilities are same for all players and may include SSS abilities, depending on lobby settings."
    "MENU_WIKI_HERO_SELECTION_Subtitle3"                      "Locked Hero"
    "MENU_WIKI_HERO_SELECTION_Text4"                          "You can lock selected hero so it doesn't change when using reroll.\nThis is convenient if you want to master specific hero or practice certain strategy.\n\nTo lock hero, right-click on it during selection."

    //=================================================================================================================
    // WIKI - Ability System
    //=================================================================================================================
    "MENU_WIKI_ABILITIES_SYSTEM_Title"                        "Ability System"
    "MENU_WIKI_ABILITIES_SYSTEM_Text1"                        "In Ancient Arena you start only with your hero's abilities, but can add abilities from other heroes during game. Maximum number of active abilities is initially limited."
    "MENU_WIKI_ABILITIES_SYSTEM_Subtitle1"                    "Getting New Abilities"
    "MENU_WIKI_ABILITIES_SYSTEM_Text2"                        "New abilities drop after certain rounds. You are offered choice of several random abilities. Some abilities are unique and rare."
    "MENU_WIKI_ABILITIES_SYSTEM_Subtitle2"                    "Reroll Book"
    "MENU_WIKI_ABILITIES_SYSTEM_Text3"                        "This item allows replacing any ability you chose with new random one.\n\nAlso exist Superior Reroll Book, SSS Reroll Book and Reroll Book Leaf.\nEach of these items has unique mechanics and special effects that distinguish it from others."
    "MENU_WIKI_ABILITIES_SYSTEM_Subtitle3"                    "Book of Paragon"
    "MENU_WIKI_ABILITIES_SYSTEM_Text4"                        "Increases active ability limit. When you reached ability maximum and want to add more - must buy this item. Available in shop for gold."

    //=================================================================================================================
    // WIKI - Items (combined category)
    //=================================================================================================================
    "MENU_WIKI_ITEMS_Title"                                   "Items"
    "MENU_WIKI_ITEMS_Text1"                                   "Complete information about item system in Ancient Arena."

    //=================================================================================================================
    // WIKI - Regular Items
    //=================================================================================================================
    "MENU_WIKI_REGULAR_ITEMS_Title"                           "Regular Items"
    "MENU_WIKI_REGULAR_ITEMS_Text1"                           "All standard Dota 2 items are available in Ancient Arena, but not all retain familiar stats, effects or abilities from regular game.\n\nAdditionally, mode features many unique custom items designed specifically for this mode, adding new possibilities and strategic options."
    "MENU_WIKI_REGULAR_ITEMS_Subtitle1"                       "Custom Items"
    "MENU_WIKI_REGULAR_ITEMS_Text2"                           "Game includes many custom items, each with unique effects and mechanics:\n\n- Hellmask — improved combination of Assault Cuirass and Satanic.\n- Force of Star — essential item for mages.\n- Enhanced Battle Fury and Dragon Lance — for dealing powerful physical damage to creeps.\n- Upgrades for Helm of the Dominator — enhance summoned creeps.\n- And many other items with unique properties.\n\nEach of these items creates new strategic possibilities and makes gameplay more diverse."
    "MENU_WIKI_REGULAR_ITEMS_Subtitle2"                       "Magic Build"
    "MENU_WIKI_REGULAR_ITEMS_Text3"                           "For magical damage definitely buy Sky Staff and Force of Star - they significantly amplify magic damage. These items are critical for casters in late rounds."
    "MENU_WIKI_REGULAR_ITEMS_Subtitle3"                       "Special Items"
    "MENU_WIKI_REGULAR_ITEMS_Text4"                           "Pay attention to Book of Paragon (increases ability limit), Reroll Book (ability retraining) and Neutral Book (additional neutral items). These items are critically important for character development."

    //=================================================================================================================
    // ВИКИПЕДИЯ - Нейтральные предметы
    //=================================================================================================================
    "MENU_WIKI_NEUTRAL_ITEMS_Title"                           "Neutral Items"
    "MENU_WIKI_NEUTRAL_ITEMS_Text1"                           "Neutral item system in Ancient Arena works differently than in regular Dota 2. You craft them yourself in special interface. All neutral items you replace are saved and moved to shop, to 'Neutrals' section."
    "MENU_WIKI_NEUTRAL_ITEMS_Subtitle1"                       "Tier System"
    "MENU_WIKI_NEUTRAL_ITEMS_Text2"                           "Neutral items are divided into 5 tiers (Tier 1-5). Each new tier unlocks at certain rounds. Upon reaching required round you can craft one item of that tier by choosing artifact and enchantments."
    "MENU_WIKI_NEUTRAL_ITEMS_Subtitle2"                       "Neutral Book"
    "MENU_WIKI_NEUTRAL_ITEMS_Text3"                           "If you were unlucky with tier 5 neutral item or want to get additional neutrals - buy Neutral Book in shop. It allows crafting another neutral item of current tier."
    "MENU_WIKI_NEUTRAL_ITEMS_Subtitle3"                       "Selection Strategy"
    "MENU_WIKI_NEUTRAL_ITEMS_Text4"                           "When choosing neutral item consider your role and playstyle. For physical damage choose items with attack and crit, for magical - with intelligence and mana regen. Tier 5 items are especially powerful and can drastically change your effectiveness."

    //=================================================================================================================
    // WIKI - Game Modes
    //=================================================================================================================
    "MENU_WIKI_GAME_MODES_Title"                              "Game Modes"
    "MENU_WIKI_GAME_MODES_Text1"                              "Ancient Arena has several round types: regular creep waves, minigames, bosses and special events."
    "MENU_WIKI_GAME_MODES_Subtitle1"                          "Regular Waves"
    "MENU_WIKI_GAME_MODES_Text2"                              "Standard mode - waves of various creeps attack your base. Creep composition changes from round to round. After defense time expires, creeps gradually become stronger every second:\n- their damage increases,\n- movement speed rises,\n- other stats grow.\n\nAdditionally, they gain unobstructed movement, making them especially dangerous.\n\nAt certain rounds bosses appear — significantly more powerful creeps requiring special attention and strategic approach to kill."
    "MENU_WIKI_GAME_MODES_Subtitle2"                          "Minigames"
    "MENU_WIKI_GAME_MODES_Text3"                              "Periodically voting for round mode occurs. Available: Arena Mode (PvP arena), Pudge Wars (hook battles), Mirana Wars (arrow battles). Winning minigame grants bonuses to entire team."
    "MENU_WIKI_GAME_MODES_Subtitle3"                          "Duels"
    "MENU_WIKI_GAME_MODES_Text4"                              "Throughout game players randomly face each other in duels, testing their strength against heroes, not creeps.\n\nDuels are key game element. After round 60 (configurable in lobby) duel losses start taking player lives.\n\nIf loser has no lives left, they start receiving strong negative effects (debuffs), making loss especially dangerous and requiring careful strategy."

    //=================================================================================================================
    // WIKI - Advanced Mechanics
    //=================================================================================================================
    "MENU_WIKI_ADVANCED_MECHANICS_Title"                      "Advanced Mechanics"
    "MENU_WIKI_ADVANCED_MECHANICS_Text1"                      "Additional mechanics and possibilities are available for experienced players."
    "MENU_WIKI_ADVANCED_MECHANICS_Subtitle1"                  "Difficulty Settings"
    "MENU_WIKI_ADVANCED_MECHANICS_Text2"                      "In lobby you can configure difficulty: number of lives (0-3), number of rerolls (0-100), number of SSS abilities at start (0-4), creep scaling speed and other parameters."
    "MENU_WIKI_ADVANCED_MECHANICS_Subtitle2"                  "Skills System"
    "MENU_WIKI_ADVANCED_MECHANICS_Text3"                      "Game has upgradeable skills system giving permanent bonuses. You can view them by hovering cursor over special panel. Skills persist throughout entire game and affect your playstyle."
    "MENU_WIKI_ADVANCED_MECHANICS_Subtitle3"                  "Creep Summoning"
    "MENU_WIKI_ADVANCED_MECHANICS_Text4"                      "After round 60 (configurable in lobby) players gain ability to send creeps to their enemies.\n\nEach creep has unique abilities that can hinder opponents and create additional difficulties.\n\nSent creep appears at every player except sender, and will participate in combat every subsequent round."

    //=================================================================================================================
    // WIKI - Progression and Rewards
    //=================================================================================================================
    "MENU_WIKI_PROGRESSION_Title"                             "Progression and Rewards"
    "MENU_WIKI_PROGRESSION_Text1"                             "Ancient Arena has progression system that motivates to play and improve your results."
    "MENU_WIKI_PROGRESSION_Subtitle1"                         "Experience and Rating System"
    "MENU_WIKI_PROGRESSION_Text2"                             "Level up Battle Pass and receive rewards that update each season.\nExperience system for Battle Pass and rating is specially tuned for long games so progress is meaningful.\nLevel up your best heroes, just like in Dota Plus, and receive additional bonuses for mastery."
    "MENU_WIKI_PROGRESSION_Subtitle2"                         "Battle Pass"
    "MENU_WIKI_PROGRESSION_Text3"                             "Battle Pass grants many advantages: ability to ban heroes and abilities, unique voice phrases, pauses, damage statistics, free taunts, new arenas and effects. Arsenal of rewards and content will be regularly balanced and updated to maintain interest and diversity in game. Available for 1, 3 or 6 months."
    "MENU_WIKI_PROGRESSION_Subtitle3"                         "Leaderboards and Seasons"
    "MENU_WIKI_PROGRESSION_Text4"                             "Compete with other players in ranking table.\nReceive rewards for achievements at season end.\nEach season leaderboard updates, reflecting current results.\n\nParticipate in tournaments and prove you're the best player in our game!"

    //=================================================================================================================
    // WIKI - AI Helper
    //=================================================================================================================
    "MENU_WIKI_AI_HELPER_Title"                               "AI Helper"
    "MENU_WIKI_AI_HELPER_Text1"                               "Intelligent assistant for getting information about game."
    "MENU_WIKI_AI_HELPER_Welcome"                             "Hello! I'm Ancient Arena AI assistant. Ask questions about game mechanics, heroes, items and strategies!"
    "MENU_WIKI_AI_HELPER_Note"                                "Example questions: 'How do neutral items work?', 'Which heroes are best for beginners?', 'What is Book of Paragon?'"
    "MENU_WIKI_AI_HELPER_Placeholder"                         "Ask question about game..."
    "MENU_WIKI_AI_HELPER_Send"                                "Send"

    //=================================================================================================================
    // WIKI - FAQ
    //=================================================================================================================
    "MENU_WIKI_FAQ_Title"                                      "Frequently Asked Questions"
    "MENU_WIKI_FAQ_Q1"                                         "How to get more abilities?"
    "MENU_WIKI_FAQ_A1"                                         "Buy Book of Paragon in shop. It increases active ability limit."
    "MENU_WIKI_FAQ_Q2"                                         "What to do if not enough gold?"
    "MENU_WIKI_FAQ_A2"                                         "Kill creeps more efficiently, participate in minigames and defeat bosses - they give more gold."
    "MENU_WIKI_FAQ_Q3"                                         "How to change ability?"
    "MENU_WIKI_FAQ_A3"                                         "Use Reroll Book which can be purchased in shop."
    "MENU_WIKI_FAQ_Q4"                                         "When do neutral items appear?"
    "MENU_WIKI_FAQ_A4"                                         "Neutral items of different tiers unlock at certain rounds. You craft them yourself in special interface."
    "MENU_WIKI_FAQ_Q5"                                         "Why do I start defending creeps later than other players?"
    "MENU_WIKI_FAQ_A5"                                         "New system introduced — creep wave defense happens in turns: players go out in groups with 10 second intervals."
    "MENU_WIKI_FAQ_Q6"                                         "Why was this mechanic created?"
    "MENU_WIKI_FAQ_A6"                                         "To reduce lag during mass creep killing."
    "MENU_WIKI_FAQ_Q7"                                         "How to get Battle Pass?"
    "MENU_WIKI_FAQ_A7"                                         "Battle Pass can be purchased in special game menu. It grants many advantages and supports developer."


